Start up node
npm start from terminal. Make sure the terminal is in the workspace and not a specific folder.

Close node
Ctrl C

Push to bit bucket
git add-A
git status

how to get rid of hearts
start mongo shell: mongo
use heartsDB
db.userlist.remove({})


add hearts:
from the / view, bring up browser console.
run:
generateRandomSet(numberOfRecords, emptiesBoolean)  //emptiesBoolean true to make empty hearts randomly, false for all 'claimed' hearts


